  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nThe `vipercoin.v.py` contract example returning `False` instead of `throw/assert` in function:\r\n\r\n- `transfer()`\r\n- `transferFrom()`\r\n\r\nAs defined in [ERC20 standard](https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/blob/master/EIPS/eip-20-token-standard.md#transfer), those 2 function should throw in case of insufficient fund.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nChange the logic to using assertion or use viper built-in `num256_sub`/`num256_add` that will automatically throw if substraction result is negative.\r\n\r\n#### Cute Animal Picture\r\n\r\n![picity pic](https://i.pinimg.com/736x/55/fd/40/55fd40c913214f6f38922cbfd366c71a--cute-animal-illustration-animal-illustrations.jpg)\r\n",
